<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-23T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="11" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/4562: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-23T18:00:00-04:00">February 23, 1935—6
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 7:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>14. My telegram No. 12, February 21, 3 p.m. I have just been informed
                                by telephone by the Foreign Office that a communication has been
                                transmitted to the League announcing Paraguay’s withdrawal.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>